Package com.example.freeturilo.storage

Class StorageRunnable<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.example.freeturilo.storage.StorageRunnable<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of payload retrieved within the transaction or Boolean if no payload is retrieved
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Runnable
    public class StorageRunnable<T>
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Runnable
    A runnable performing an asynchronous storage data transaction.

    Object of this class performs an asynchronous transaction with a callback and an error handler. It can be easily customized and wrapped in a Thread.

    Version:
    1.0.0

    • Method Detail

      • run

        public void run()
        Runs the transaction synchronously. If set, calls the callback in the main thread on successful transaction finish. Otherwise, if set, handles transaction errors with handler in the main thread.
        Specified by:
